===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In oracle bone inscriptions, {{liushu|p|nocap=yes}} of a net, originally the same character as {{zh-l|*𠦒}} and {{zh-l|*畢}}. In bronze inscriptions, the phonetic component {{och-l|今}} was added, making the character {{liushu|psc|adj=yse|nocap=yes|pron={{och-retrieve-pron}}}}. This form was borrowed for its modern meaning, and the original meaning of "capture" came to be represented by {{och-l|擒}}. 

In the modern form, {{zh-l|*今}} has corrupted into {{zh-l|*人}} and {{zh-l|*𠦒}} into {{zh-l|*离}}. Compare with {{zh-l|*畢}}.

